🚀 Steps to Run / Simulate the Pipeline

This project is implemented using Dataform + BigQuery, with SQLX models stored in GitHub.
The pipeline can be executed by connecting the repository to Dataform and running the models.

🔹 Prerequisites

Before running the pipeline, ensure:

Google Cloud Project with BigQuery enabled
Dataform access (Cloud Dataform or Dataform UI)
GitHub repository access
Permission to create BigQuery datasets
(Optional) jq installed for JSON → NDJSON conversion
🔹 Step 1: Clone / Connect GitHub Repository

The SQLX transformation logic is stored in GitHub.

Open Dataform
Create a new repository
Connect to this GitHub repo
Select default branch (main)
Open workspace

Dataform will automatically detect:

definitions/
  silver/
  gold/
  diamond/

These .sqlx files define the full pipeline.

🔹 Step 2: Create BigQuery Dataset (Same as Project)

Create datasets in BigQuery matching the pipeline layers:

Create the following datasets:

raw
silver
gold
diamond

Example:

your_project.raw_data
your_project.silver
your_project.gold
your_project.diamond

These datasets are referenced inside the SQLX models.

🔹 Step 3: Load Sample Raw Data

Upload sample datasets from data_samples/ into BigQuery:

File	Target Table
ga4_events_feb.json	raw.ga4
crm_db.orders.json	raw.crm
ads_data_010226_140226.csv	raw.ads

Enable schema auto-detection or align with expected schema.

🔹 Step 3.1 : Convert JSON to NDJSON

If CRM data is provided as Mongo-style JSON array, convert to NDJSON before upload.

jq -c '.[]' n_crm_db.orders.json > crm_ndjson.json

Upload:

crm_ndjson.json → raw.crm

This format is preferred for BigQuery ingestion and incremental loads.

🔹 Step 4: Run Dataform Pipeline

In Dataform:

Click Start Execution
Select Run All
Dataform resolves dependencies automatically
Execution order:
Silver → Gold → Diamond

Dataform will run:

silver/ga4.sqlx
silver/crm.sqlx
silver/ads.sqlx
gold/int_campaign_performance.sqlx
diamond.fct_campaign_performance.sqlx

🔹 Step 5: Pipeline Layers
Silver Layer

Cleans and standardizes raw datasets:

Fix date formats
Remove invalid records
Normalize schema

Output:

silver.ga4
silver.crm
silver.ads
Gold Layer

Business transformation layer:

Join GA4 + CRM + Ads
Calculate conversions
Calculate revenue
Apply business logic

Output:

gold.int_campaign_performance

Diamond Layer

Final analytics-ready table:

Campaign-level aggregation
KPI calculations
Net revenue logic

Output:

diamond.fct_campaign_performance.sqlx

🔹 Step 6: Validate Results

Verify final table:

diamond.fct_campaign_performance.sqlx

Check:

No duplicate campaign_id + date
No null key fields
Revenue calculations correct
Spend vs conversion consistency
🔹 Incremental Logic

The pipeline supports incremental execution:

Date-based filtering
Only new records processed
Idempotent execution
Prevents full refresh

Implemented inside SQLX models using Dataform incremental logic.

🔹 Automating the Pipeline (Scheduler)

The Dataform pipeline can be automated using Dataform Scheduler.

Steps:

Open Dataform repository
Go to Schedules
Create new schedule
Select Run All Actions
Set frequency (Daily / Hourly)
Choose execution time
Save

Example:

Schedule: Daily
Time: 02:00 AM
Execution: Run All

This will automatically:

Ingest → Transform → Load → Build Final Table

No manual execution required.

✅ Final Output

Final table:

diamond.fct_campaign_performance.sqlx

Contains:

campaign_id
date
spend
clicks
impressions
conversions
revenue
returns
net_revenue

This dataset enables analysis of true campaign performance and profitability using a fully automated Dataform pipeline.
